						               													<description>Spanish game based on a ficticional battle between the &amp;quot;Attack Group of KRON&amp;quot; and the &amp;quot;Omega Commando&amp;quot; of 'The Leader'.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Released by 'Star Play S.L.' Publisher at early '80s, this game probably combines the titles of &amp;quot;Krull&amp;quot; (1983) and &amp;quot;Tron&amp;quot; (1982) films and was another Sci-Fi game resulting of the great success of Star Wars Trilogy.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The game components are:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- 01x Rulebook&amp;#10;- 01x Quick-introduction sheet&amp;#10;- 01x Map representing outer space and a cosmic shuttle&amp;#10;- 14x Warriors (7 for each player) including The Leader / Kron&amp;#10;- 01x Six-Sided (D6) Dice&amp;#10;- 01x Dice Cup&amp;#10;&amp;#10;They are 4 types of different troops:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;- Heroes: Kron Strength 5 &amp;amp; El L&amp;iacute;der - Strength 6&amp;#10;- Laser Gunner: The only one who can attack from far, but need to be his Hero in game to use it - Strength 1 / Shoot 4&amp;#10;- Android: The worst warrior type Strength 2&amp;#10;- Humanoid: The best in melee fight) Strength 4&amp;#10;&amp;#10;How to play:&amp;#10;&amp;#10;We have a space shuttle in the middle of the map. Each team, has 5 asterisks in the outer space. They are the starting point of their troops. The players will have 7 warriors, and they have to decide which 5 will start the battle. After it, the game secuence is: move (1 or 2 hexas) any of all of their troops, shoot with the gunners, melee attacks and call for reinforcements.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You can fight into the shuttle -there is an aditional asterisk on it that you can use for warriors entry after occupying the star point- or in the outer space, but you can&amp;acute;t cross the space ship except from the entrance / exit doors.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The player who conquest all the enemy's asteriks will be the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
